revision.text: ==Northern Kurdish== ===Etymology=== {{root|kmr|ine-pro|*swep-}} From {{inh|kmr|ira-pro|*hwápnas}}, from {{inh|kmr|iir-pro|*swápnas}}, ultimately from {{der|kmr|ine-pro|*swépnos||sleep}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*swep-||to sleep}}. Cognate with {{cog|en|sweven||dream, vision}}. ===Pronunciation=== * {{kmr-IPA}} ===Noun=== {{kmr-noun|f}} # {{qualifier|uncountable}} [[sleep]] ====Derived terms==== * {{l|kmr|xew kirin}} ====Related terms==== * {{l|kmr|xewn}} {{cln|kmr|three-letter words}} ---- ==Wolof== ===Verb=== {{head|wo|verb}} # to [[happen]] ===Noun=== {{wo-noun|mi}} # [[occasion]], [[ceremony]] ===References=== {{cite-book |author=Omar Ka |chapter= |title=Nanu Dégg Wolof |publisher=National African Language Resource Center |year=2018 |page=259 |isbn=978-1-59703-017-5}}
